<div class="block px-5 w-full faqs-section lg:px-10 xl:px-15" style="background-color:#fdfcfb;" data-title="Your 2026 beauty questions">
        <div class="container !px-0">
            <div class="flex flex-col gap-10 mx-auto faqs-inner">
                
                    
                    <h2 class="text-center font-extrabold" style="color:#0f3062;">
                        Your 2026 beauty questions
                    </h2>
                
    
                
                <div class="flex flex-col gap-6 faqs-wrapper" x-data="{ active: &#39;&#39; }">
                    
                        
                <details x-effect="active != &#39;faq-1&#39; &amp;&amp; $el.removeAttribute(&#39;open&#39;)" id="faq_yfrPCN" class="w-full faq" style="background:#f8f5f1;">
                    <summary class="p-6 cursor-pointer" style="color:#0f3062;" @click="active = &#39;faq-1&#39;">
                        <div class="inline-flex w-[calc(100%-6px)] items-center justify-between gap-2.5 faq__question">
                            <strong>How were these 2026 skincare and beauty holy grails chosen?</strong>
                            <span aria-hidden="true" class="w-2 h-2 summary-icon transition-300"><svg width="100%" viewBox="0 0 15 9" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
    <path d="M1.58594 1.04285L7.50024 6.95715L13.4146 1.04285" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.97144" stroke-linecap="round"></path>
</svg></span>
                        </div>
                    </summary>
                    <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-base rte" style="color:#0f3062;">
                        <p>This edit brings together Skin Cupid bestsellers, community favourites, and products our team genuinely reaches for. Each product is chosen for how it performs in real routines, not just trends.</p>
                    </div>
                </details>
            
                <details x-effect="active != &#39;faq-2&#39; &amp;&amp; $el.removeAttribute(&#39;open&#39;)" id="faq_e8rCqd" class="w-full faq" style="background:#f8f5f1;">
                    <summary class="p-6 cursor-pointer" style="color:#0f3062;" @click="active = &#39;faq-2&#39;">
                        <div class="inline-flex w-[calc(100%-6px)] items-center justify-between gap-2.5 faq__question">
                            <strong>What makes Korean skincare different from other skincare?</strong>
                            <span aria-hidden="true" class="w-2 h-2 summary-icon transition-300"><svg width="100%" viewBox="0 0 15 9" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
    <path d="M1.58594 1.04285L7.50024 6.95715L13.4146 1.04285" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.97144" stroke-linecap="round"></path>
</svg></span>
                        </div>
                    </summary>
                    <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-base rte" style="color:#0f3062;">
                        <p>Korean Skincare aims to heal and strengthen your natural skin barrier, giving your skin a healthy glow. To accomplish this, the skincare tends to be more gentle to nourish the skin, with natural ingredients often featured prominently in formulas. Additionally, Korean skincare really emphasises the importance of layering, this allows different product types to penetrate deeper into the skin, target different concerns, as well as effectively cleanse, prep the skin, and ensure better absorption of the product. The term quick-fix doesnt exist in a Korean skincare routine  its all about consistency, dedication, and maintaining long-term skin health.&nbsp;</p><p>On the other hand, Western Skincare focuses on the overall appearance of the skin, with a preference towards more active chemical ingredients that deliver results. Layering skincare is less popular, with some products aiming to substitute quite a few steps at once for faster application. While innovation in Western skincare is present, Koreas ultra-competitive skincare industry contains thousands of companies that are constantly competing with one another, resulting in greater innovation and affordability. </p>
                    </div>
                </details>
            
                <details x-effect="active != &#39;faq-3&#39; &amp;&amp; $el.removeAttribute(&#39;open&#39;)" id="faq_LUYK87" class="w-full faq" style="background:#f8f5f1;">
                    <summary class="p-6 cursor-pointer" style="color:#0f3062;" @click="active = &#39;faq-3&#39;">
                        <div class="inline-flex w-[calc(100%-6px)] items-center justify-between gap-2.5 faq__question">
                            Where to start with Korean Skincare?
                            <span aria-hidden="true" class="w-2 h-2 summary-icon transition-300"><svg width="100%" viewBox="0 0 15 9" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
    <path d="M1.58594 1.04285L7.50024 6.95715L13.4146 1.04285" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.97144" stroke-linecap="round"></path>
</svg></span>
                        </div>
                    </summary>
                    <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-base rte" style="color:#0f3062;">
                        <p>If you are a K-Beauty beginner, we recommend starting with a simple 4-step routine that includes a cleanser, a serum, a moisturiser, and a sunscreen. We recommend starting small because if your skin is not used to many actives and layering, the sudden introduction of a 10-step routine that contains powerful products may overwhelm your skin, or cause it to break out. Slowly increasing the number of products in your routine will also make it easier for you to determine if a product is not suitable for your skin. </p>
                    </div>
                </details>
            
                <details x-effect="active != &#39;faq-4&#39; &amp;&amp; $el.removeAttribute(&#39;open&#39;)" id="faq_FktfwY" class="w-full faq" style="background:#f8f5f1;">
                    <summary class="p-6 cursor-pointer" style="color:#0f3062;" @click="active = &#39;faq-4&#39;">
                        <div class="inline-flex w-[calc(100%-6px)] items-center justify-between gap-2.5 faq__question">
                            <strong>Do I need a full multi-step routine to see results?</strong>
                            <span aria-hidden="true" class="w-2 h-2 summary-icon transition-300"><svg width="100%" viewBox="0 0 15 9" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
    <path d="M1.58594 1.04285L7.50024 6.95715L13.4146 1.04285" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.97144" stroke-linecap="round"></path>
</svg></span>
                        </div>
                    </summary>
                    <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-base rte" style="color:#0f3062;">
                        <p>Not at all. Results come from consistency and choosing the right products for your skin, not the number of steps. This edit is designed so you can pick what works for you and skip what doesnt.</p>
                    </div>
                </details>
            
                <details x-effect="active != &#39;faq-5&#39; &amp;&amp; $el.removeAttribute(&#39;open&#39;)" id="faq_38gjFC" class="w-full faq" style="background:#f8f5f1;">
                    <summary class="p-6 cursor-pointer" style="color:#0f3062;" @click="active = &#39;faq-5&#39;">
                        <div class="inline-flex w-[calc(100%-6px)] items-center justify-between gap-2.5 faq__question">
                            Does Korean skincare work for everyone?
                            <span aria-hidden="true" class="w-2 h-2 summary-icon transition-300"><svg width="100%" viewBox="0 0 15 9" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
    <path d="M1.58594 1.04285L7.50024 6.95715L13.4146 1.04285" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.97144" stroke-linecap="round"></path>
</svg></span>
                        </div>
                    </summary>
                    <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-base rte" style="color:#0f3062;">
                        <p>Yes! Korean skincare covers the full spectrum of skin types and concerns, making it easy to put together a routine that suits your skin. However, we recommend you introduce new products into your routine gradually, so as not to overwhelm your skin and cause a negative reaction.&nbsp; </p>
                    </div>
                </details>
            
                <details x-effect="active != &#39;faq-6&#39; &amp;&amp; $el.removeAttribute(&#39;open&#39;)" id="faq_TQUVcg" class="w-full faq" style="background:#f8f5f1;">
                    <summary class="p-6 cursor-pointer" style="color:#0f3062;" @click="active = &#39;faq-6&#39;">
                        <div class="inline-flex w-[calc(100%-6px)] items-center justify-between gap-2.5 faq__question">
                            <strong>How can I upgrade my skincare routine for 2026?</strong>
                            <span aria-hidden="true" class="w-2 h-2 summary-icon transition-300"><svg width="100%" viewBox="0 0 15 9" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
    <path d="M1.58594 1.04285L7.50024 6.95715L13.4146 1.04285" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.97144" stroke-linecap="round"></path>
</svg></span>
                        </div>
                    </summary>
                    <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-base rte" style="color:#0f3062;">
                        <p>Upgrading your skincare routine for 2026 starts with moving away from excess and focusing on intention. This edit is designed as a framework, highlighting the essentials that support hydration, barrier health, and targeted treatment without overcomplicating your routine. By selecting high-quality products that complement each other, you can establish a routine that feels more intentional, easier to maintain, and better suited to long-term skin health.</p><p></p>
                    </div>
                </details>
            
                        
                    
                
